

"Interactive Fiction Things" by "Katelyn Gigante (@Silasary)"

The story creation year is 2016.
The story headline is "Things from Parser Fiction"
The story description is "Searching ifdb.tads.org for Parser Fiction, and tweeting excerpts from their source code."
Release along with the source text.

Chapter 1 - The Idea

A Parser Fiction is a type of game. A Parser Fiction is sometimes released with its Source Code.
Source Code is a type of text file.  Source Code belongs to a game.

Understand the command "tweet" as something new.
Tweeting is an action.

Understand "tweet [something]" as tweeting.

Instead of playing a Parser Fiction, tweet its source code.